5000|$|Spunbond {{has been}} {{combined}} with melt-blown nonwovens, conforming {{them into a}} layered product called SMS (spun-melt-spun). Melt-blown nonwovens have extremely fine fiber diameters but are not strong fabrics. SMS fabrics, made completely from PP are water-repellent and fine enough to serve as disposable fabrics. Melt-blown is often used as filter media, being able to capture very fine particles. <b>Spunlaid</b> is bonded by either resin or thermally. Regarding the bonding of <b>Spunlaid,</b> Rieter [...] has launched {{a new generation of}} nonwovens called Spunjet. In fact, Spunjet is the bonding of the <b>Spunlaid</b> filaments thanks to the hydroentanglement.|$|E
